source_code.code:
public class Outer {
    private void outerPrivateMethod() {}
    private class Inner {
        void foo() {
            outerPrivateMethod();
        }
    }
}

Bug.WithStack:
Consider the following case:

public class Outer {
    private void outerPrivateMethod() {}
    private class Inner {
        void foo() {
            outerPrivateMethod();
        }
    }
}

Moving the Inner class out will result in a compile error, since the outer
private method is not visible. There should be at least a warning on the preview
page. The same happens with private fields.

Another solution would be to add public wrapper methods automatically for
private field and method access. This should only happen only on user request
though.
