public class Foo {
    public static class Bar extends Foo {}
    private void foo() {}
    private void bar() {
        Foo foo= new Bar();
        foo.foo();
    }
}

Bug.WithStack:
Consider the following (admittably rare) case:

public class Foo {
    public static class Bar extends Foo {}
    private void foo() {}
    private void bar() {
        Foo foo= new Bar();
        foo.foo();
    }
}

When moving Bar to top level Foo does not compile, since it refers to a method
which is private to Foo, but through a class which is no longer in the scope of
Foo. There should at least be a warning on the preview page.
